  "text": "19 We here write only the bosonic part for simplicity. [CITATION_1] We impose the Dirichlet boundary condition on X 1 , \u00b7 \u00b7 \u00b7 , X 5 and X 9 at \u03c3 = 0. For the other boundary \u03c3 = \u03c0, we impose the Neumann boundary condition on X 0 , \u00b7 \u00b7 \u00b7 , X 5 and the Dirichlet boundary condition on X 6 , \u00b7 \u00b7 \u00b7 , X 9 , corresponding to the existence of the D5-brane. From the condition (23), we find that our BPS strings end on the D3-brane with a \"slope\" depending on the electric field F 08 . To see this explicitly, we estimate \u03b4X 8 /\u03b4X 9 along the string world-sheet. Note that our D5-D3 strings cannot have non-vanishing momentum in the x 9 -direction. This implies that for BPS D5-D3 strings X 9 (\u03c4, \u03c3) has no \u03c4 -dependence. [CITATION_2] Therefore, we can identify \u03b4X 8 /\u03b4X 9 with",
